<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028448>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Cheiracanthium iranicum sp. n., holotype male. (a) Dorsal habitus. (b) Prosoma, frontal view. (c) Right palp, ventral view (mirrored image). (d) Ibid, SEM graph (mirrored image). (e) Tibia of male palp, lateral view. (f) Retrolateral tibial apophysis. Abbreviations:C – conductor, CF – cymbial fold; CS – cymbial spur; E – embolus; EB – embolus base; PTA – prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA – retrolateral tibial apophysis; TA – tegular apophysis. Scale bars: a – 1.0, b – 0.5, c – 0.2, d–f – 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5028448/files/figure.png" .

